<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="409" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,150,1114]" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,150,176]" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. The only Neotropical species of the subgenus 
<emphasis box="[796,815,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">C</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[837,1036,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">Haematomyidium</emphasis>
) with the following combination of characters: females with flagellomeres 4–12 subequal in length; sensilla coeloconica on flagellomeres 1, 6–8; palpal segment 3 swollen, with moderately large and deep sensory pit; poststigmatic pale spots in r 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1172,1180,241,255]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">3</subScript>
separated; cell m 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1372,1380,241,255]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">1</subScript>
with two pale spots, distal one well separated from wing margin; cell m 
<subScript attach="left" box="[891,899,277,291]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">2</subScript>
with pale spot posterior to medial fork and with an elongate pale spot anterior to cubital fork; macrotrichia sparse on distal third of cells r 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1158,1166,313,327]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">3</subScript>
and m 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1244,1252,313,327]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">1</subScript>
. Male paramere stem very slender, with no trace of ventral lobe and apex pointed with lateral fringe of fine hairs; distal portion of aedeagus broadly expanded, with three pointed lobes of subequal lengths.
</paragraph>
