<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="409" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,150,1114]" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,619,645]" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">Remarks</emphasis>
. The cell m 
<subScript attach="left" box="[444,452,637,651]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">2</subScript>
with an elongate pale spot anterior to the cubital fork, and the absence of macrotrichia on cells m 
<subScript attach="left" box="[265,273,673,687]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">2</subScript>
, cua 
<subScript attach="left" box="[326,334,673,687]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">1</subScript>
and anal cell are clearly shown in the wing illustration that accompanies the original description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fox" authorityYear="1946" box="[151,285,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Culicoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="409" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hoffmani">
<emphasis box="[151,170,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[185,285,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">hoffmani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Fox, I." box="[328,447,691,717]" pageId="8" pageNumber="409" pagination="248 - 258" refId="ref4730" refString="Fox, I. (1946) A review of the species of biting midges or Culicoides from the Caribbean Region (Diptera: Ceratopogonidae). Annals of the Entomological Society of America, 39, 248 - 258. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / aesa / 39.2.248" type="journal article" year="1946">Fox (1946</bibRefCitation>
, page 253, 
<figureCitation box="[576,644,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–12" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[180,1408,190,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-25@4.[170,1417,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7–12. Culicoides dellapei n. sp. Holotype female, 7–12. 7 head. 8 palpus. 9 legs. 10 wing. 11 abdomen. 12 detail of spermathecae. Scale bars = 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4456611" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4456611/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
). Moreover, the authors specifically stated “...with macrotrichia in the apical region”. The wing photograph included in the Wing Atlas of the Neotropical species by 
<bibRefCitation author="Wirth, W. W. &amp; Dyce, A. L. &amp; Spinelli, G. R." box="[1226,1436,727,753]" pageId="8" pageNumber="409" pagination="1 - 72" refId="ref5354" refString="Wirth, W. W., Dyce, A. L. &amp; Spinelli, G. R. (1988) An atlas of wing photographs, with a summary of the numerical characters of the Neotropical species of Culicoides (Diptera: Ceratopogonidae). Contributions of the American Entomological Institute, 25, 1 - 72." type="journal article" year="1988">Wirth et al. (1988)</bibRefCitation>
coincides with the illustration in the original description.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,150,1114]" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">
It is worth remarking that 
<bibRefCitation author="Wirth, W. W. &amp; Blanton, F. S." box="[491,761,798,825]" pageId="8" pageNumber="409" pagination="186 - 190" refId="ref5249" refString="Wirth, W. W. &amp; Blanton, F. S. (1956) Redescription of four species of Neotropical Culicoides of the debilipalpis group (Diptera: Heleidae). Journal of the Washington Academy of Sciences, 46, 186 - 190." type="journal article" year="1956">Wirth &amp; Blanton (1956)</bibRefCitation>
incorrectly provided wing illustrations showing the absence of a pale spot anterior to the cubital fork in cell m 
<subScript attach="left" box="[713,721,853,867]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">2</subScript>
, and the macrotrichia extending in two rows to base of cell m 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1421,1429,853,867]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">2</subScript>
. This wrong wing illustration was also included in the revision of the genus from 
<collectingCountry box="[1062,1151,871,897]" name="Panama" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">Panama</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Wirth, W. W. &amp; Blanton, F. S." box="[1165,1424,870,897]" pageId="8" pageNumber="409" pagination="237 - 482" refId="ref5296" refString="Wirth, W. W. &amp; Blanton, F. S. (1959) Biting midges of the genus Culicoides from Panama (Diptera: Heleidae). Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 109, 237 - 482. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.109 - 3415.237" type="journal article" year="1959">Wirth &amp; Blanton 1959</bibRefCitation>
), but in the key 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fox" authorityYear="1946" box="[310,442,907,933]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Culicoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="409" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hoffmani">
<emphasis box="[310,329,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[342,442,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">hoffmani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
correctly keys out in couplet 76, where species that have a pale spot in cell m 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1309,1317,925,939]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">2</subScript>
anterior to the cubital fork are located. On the other hand, in the key of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lutz" authorityYear="1913" box="[858,990,943,969]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Culicoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="409" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="debilipalpis">
<emphasis box="[858,990,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">debilipalpis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group by 
<bibRefCitation author="Vitale, G. C. &amp; Wirth, W. W. &amp; Aitken, T. H. G." box="[1188,1400,943,969]" pageId="8" pageNumber="409" pagination="140 - 159" refId="ref5103" refString="Vitale, G. C., Wirth, W. W. &amp; Aitken, T. H. G. (1981) New species and records of Culicoides reared from arboreal habitats in Panama, with a synopsis of the debilipalpis group (Diptera: Ceratopogonidae). Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 83, 140 - 159." type="journal article" year="1981">
Vitale 
<emphasis box="[1261,1310,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">et al</emphasis>
. (1981)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fox" authorityYear="1946" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Culicoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="409" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hoffmani">
<emphasis box="[1411,1430,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[151,251,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">hoffmani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is incorrectly located in couplet 24 within the species that lack the mentioned pale spot.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,150,1114]" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">
Because of these misunderstandings about the proper features of the wing of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fox" authorityYear="1946" box="[1061,1194,1015,1041]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Culicoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="409" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hoffmani">
<emphasis box="[1061,1080,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1094,1194,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">hoffmani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it is indispensable to consult the original description. In this sense, the specimen examined herein perfectly agrees with the specimens described and illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Fox, I." box="[467,595,1087,1114]" pageId="8" pageNumber="409" pagination="248 - 258" refId="ref4730" refString="Fox, I. (1946) A review of the species of biting midges or Culicoides from the Caribbean Region (Diptera: Ceratopogonidae). Annals of the Entomological Society of America, 39, 248 - 258. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / aesa / 39.2.248" type="journal article" year="1946">Fox (1946)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
